      • parseSamples

        public void parseSamples()
                  throws Exception
        Parse lowest level QiimeClassifier report in the input directory. The classifier report lists 1 OTU/line with 1 column/sample, each column holds the OTU count for the QIIME ID in the column header. For each line, build a QiimeNode for each sample with a positive OTU count.

        QiimeNodes will be created using QiimeID (not SampleID) in order to match the metadata file #SampleID

        If ParserModuleImpl.isValid(OtuNode):

        1. Create ParsedSample for the OtuNodeImpl.getSampleId() if not yet created.
        2. Add the OtuNodeImpl.getCount() (1) to ParsedSample OTU count.
        Specified by:
        parseSamples in interface ParserModule
        Specified by:
        parseSamples in class ParserModuleImpl
        Throws:
        Exception - if error occurs while parsing classifier reports

      • runModule

        public void runModule()
               throws Exception
        To parse the taxonomy level reports output by QiimeClassifier:
        1. Call getInputFiles()
        2. Call initializeMaps()
        3. Call setOrderedQiimeIDs(File)
        4. Create ParsedSample for the OtuNodeImpl.getSampleId() if not yet created.
        5. Add the OtuNodeImpl.getCount() (1) to ParsedSample OTU count.

        Sample QIIME report line: (head otu_table_L2.txt):
        # Constructed from biom file #OTU ID 3A.1 6A.1 120A.1 7A.1 k__Bacteria;p__Actinobacteria 419.0 26.0 90.0 70.0

        Specified by:
        runModule in interface JavaModule
        Overrides:
        runModule in class ParserModuleImpl
        Throws:
        Exception - thrown if any runtime error occurs

      • getSampleId

        protected String getSampleId(String qiimeId)
                      throws Exception
        Get the Sample ID from qiimeIdToSampleIdMap. Qiime removes special characters with the script: BuildQiimeMapping.SCRIPT_VALIDATE_MAPPING, to create the qiimeId, which this method accepts as a parameter to lookup the Sample ID.
        Parameters:
        qiimeId - Qiime ID that was created from sample ID in a previous script
        Returns:
        sampleId Original sample ID from metadata file
        Throws:
        Exception - if the qiimeId is not found in qiimeIdToSampleIdMap

      • getSampleIdFromMappingFile

        protected String getSampleIdFromMappingFile(String qiimeId,
                                            int demuxIndex)
                                     throws Exception
        The mapping file used the original sampleId when generating the demultipled files, as recorded in mapping file column - "BioLockJFileName". Example: sampleId = gutSample_42 / qiimeId = gutSample.42 / "BioLockJFileName" = gutSample_42.fasts
        Parameters:
        qiimeId - Qiime corrected ID
        demuxIndex - Qiime mapping column index for "BioLockJFileName"
        Returns:
        Original sampleId extracted from "BioLockJFileName"
        Throws:
        Exception - if unable to get sample ID from metadata file column "BioLockJFileName"

      • initializeMaps

        protected void initializeMaps()
                       throws Exception
        Sample IDs in the original metadata file may contain restricted characters that will be replaced with a "." via "validate_mapping_file.py". The "BioLockJFileName" column will contain the original characters (and are used in the file name).
        Throws:
        Exception - if unable to initialize the maps
        See Also:
        http://qiime.org/scripts/validate_mapping_file.html

        Convenience maps are initialized to simplify lookups:

        • {@link #qiimeIdToSampleIdMap}
        • {@link #sampleIdToQiimeIdMap}
